{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Farid Matuk | embed = | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = Peru | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = Poet and educator | language = English and Spanish | nationality = American | citizenship = United States | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = This Isa Nice Neighborhood, My Daughter La Chola, The Real Horse | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = Honorable Mention in the 2011 and 2014 Arab American Book Awards, Ford Fellowship and Fulbright Fellowship | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Farid Matuk''' is an American poet and educator, born to a Peruvian father and Syrian mother in [[Peru]]. He writes in both English and Spanish, and his Spanish translations have appeared in ''Kadar Koli,'' ''Translation Review'', ''Mandorla'', and ''Bombay Gin''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poems-and-poets/poets/detail/farid-matuk#poet|title=Farid Matuk|website=www.poetryfoundation.org|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref> His poems have appeared in ''Denver Quarterly'', ''Flag + Void'', ''Iowa Review'', and ''Poetry'' and abroad in ''White Wall Review'' (Canada), ''Critical Quarterly'' (UK), and ''Poem: International English Language Quarterly'' (UK). He is currently Associate Professor of English and Creative Writing at the [[University of Arizona]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.arizona.edu/users/farid-matuk|title=Farid Matuk {{!}} Department of English|website=english.arizona.edu|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref> His book ''This Isa Nice Neighborhood (Letter Machine, 2010)'' was the recipient of an Honorable Mention in the [[Arab American Book Award|2011 Arab American Book Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.arabamericanmuseum.org/2011.book.award.winners|title=2011 Arab American Book Award Winners|website=www.arabamericanmuseum.org|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref> and was included in The Poetry Society of America's New American Poets series. ''My Daughter La Chola (Ahsata, 2013)'' received an Honorable Mention in the [[Arab American Book Award|2014 Arab American Book Awards]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.arabamericanmuseum.org/2014.book.award.winners|title=2014 Arab American Book Award Winners|website=www.arabamericanmuseum.org|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref>[[Arab American Book Award|.]] My Daughter La Chola was also named among the best books of 2013 by ''The Volta'' and by The Poetry Foundation while selections from its pages have been anthologized in ''The Best American Experimental Poetry, 2014'', ''The &Now Awards: The Best Innovative Writing Vol. 3'', and in ''Angels of the Americlypse: An Anthology of New Latino@ Writing''. He serves as poetry editor for ''Fence'' and on the editorial board for the Creative Writing Studies book series at Bloomsbury. Matuk is the recipient of both the Ford Fellowship and Fulbright Fellowship. The University of Arizona Press published his second full-length collection, ''The Real Horse'', in 2018.<ref>[https://uapress.arizona.edu/book/the-real-horse University of Arizona Press Website]</ref>
